<appendix xml:id="wiki-other" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Examples</title>
    <para>Various topics have been considered or presented in considering this standard. Some are
        described below.</para>
    <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
    <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
    <section xml:id="xml-data-file">
        <title>Example XML Data Files</title>
        <para>
            This section presents two examples of XML Data Files adhering to the cansas1d/1.0 standard.
            <indexterm>
                <primary>XML</primary>
                <secondary>cansas1d/1.0 data file</secondary>
            </indexterm>
            Thie first file (<literal>data-simple.xml</literal>) 
            is a basic example and the second file (<literal>cansas1d.xml</literal>) 
            uses almost all the allowed elements.
            In each, though, most of the data has been removed to clarify the structure.
        </para>
        <section xml:id="data-simple">
            <title>data-simple.xml</title>
            <para>
                The example data file <literal>data-simple.xml</literal>
                <indexterm>
                    <primary>XML file</primary>
                    <secondary>data-simple.xml</secondary>
                </indexterm>
                shows just the basic elements of the cansas1d/1.0 standard.  Only a 
                single data point has been shown to more clearly show the other structure.
                The data file is actually an excerpt from the
                <link
                    xlink:href="http://svn.smallangles.net/trac/canSAS/browser/1dwg/trunk/bimodal-test1.xml"
                    ><literal>bimodal-test1.xml</literal></link> example file in the main distribution.
                The stylesheet
                <indexterm><primary>XML Stylesheet</primary></indexterm>
                in <literal>data-simple.xml</literal> is very basic
                <footnote><para><link
                    xlink:href="http://svn.smallangles.net/trac/canSAS/browser/1dwg/trunk/bimodal-test1.xml"
                    ><literal>http://svn.smallangles.net/trac/canSAS/browser/1dwg/trunk/bimodal-test1.xml</literal></link></para></footnote>
                data file.
            </para>
            <indexterm>
                <primary>XML</primary>
                <secondary>cansas1d/1.0 data file</secondary>
            </indexterm>
            <example>
                <title><citetitle>data-simple.xml</citetitle></title>
                <programlisting language="xml" linenumbering="numbered">
                    <textobject>
                        <textdata fileref="data-simple.xml"/>
                    </textobject>
                </programlisting>
            </example>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="data-cansas1d">
            <title>cansas1d.xml</title>
            <para>
                The example data file <literal>cansas1d.xml</literal> 
                <indexterm>
                    <primary>XML file</primary>
                    <secondary>cansas1d.xml</secondary>
                </indexterm>
                shows examples
                of most of the elements of the cansas1d/1.0 standard.  Only a single data 
                point has been shown to more clearly show the other structure.
                <footnote><para><link
                    xlink:href="http://svn.smallangles.net/trac/canSAS/browser/1dwg/trunk/cansas1d.xml"
                    ><literal>http://svn.smallangles.net/trac/canSAS/browser/1dwg/trunk/cansas1d.xml</literal></link></para></footnote>
            </para>
            <indexterm>
                <primary>XML</primary>
                <secondary>cansas1d/1.0 data file</secondary>
            </indexterm>
            <!-- too long for a DocBook "example" -->
            <informalexample>
                <!--<title><citetitle>cansas1d.xml</citetitle></title>-->
                <programlisting language="xml" linenumbering="numbered">
                    <textobject>
                        <textdata fileref="../../cansas1d.xml"/>
                    </textobject>
                </programlisting>
            </informalexample>
        </section>
    </section>
    <section xml:id="xml-stylesheet">
        <title>Example XML Stylesheets</title>
        <para>
            This section presents examples of XML Stylesheets 
            <indexterm significance="preferred">
                <primary>XML Stylesheet</primary>
            </indexterm>
            useful for the cansas1d/1.0 standard.  
            XML Stylesheets (XSLT) 
            <indexterm>
                <primary>XSLT</primary>
                <see>XML Stylesheet</see>
            </indexterm>
            are used to transform XML documents into 
            other documents such as XML documents, xhtml documents, or even ASCII text.
            XML stylesheets also can be used to extract metadata
            <indexterm><primary>metadata</primary></indexterm>
            from XML files.
            <indexterm>
                <primary>XML Stylesheet</primary>
            </indexterm>
        </para>
        <section xml:id="xsl-ascii3col">
            <title>ascii3col.xsl</title>
            <para>
                The <literal>ascii3col.xsl</literal> 
                <indexterm>
                    <primary>file</primary>
                    <secondary>xsl</secondary>
                    <see>XML Stylesheet</see>
                </indexterm>
                stylesheet displays 
                all the <literal>Idata</literal> blocks in a cansas1d/1.0 file
                in 3-column ASCII form.  Be careful using this stylesheet
                on files with multiple <literal>SASdata</literal> or
                <literal>SASentry</literal> blocks since this stylesheet
                assumes there is only one of each of these.  While it
                is the most common case to have only one of each, some of
                the examples have multiple data sets.  This stylesheet will
                concatenate all of the <literal>Idata</literal>.
            </para>
            <indexterm>
                <primary>XML Stylesheet</primary>
                <secondary>ascii3col.xsl</secondary>
            </indexterm>
            <example>
                <title><citetitle>ascii3col.xsl</citetitle></title>
                <programlisting language="xml" linenumbering="numbered">
                    <textobject>
                        <textdata fileref="ascii3col.xsl"/>
                    </textobject>
                </programlisting>
            </example>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="xsl-cansas1d">
            <title>cansasxml-html.xsl</title>
            <para>
                The <literal>cansasxml-html.xsl</literal> 
                <indexterm>
                    <primary>file</primary>
                    <secondary>xsl</secondary>
                    <see>XML Stylesheet</see>
                </indexterm>
                is the standard XSL stylesheet for cansas1d/1.0 files.
                It shows all available <literal>SASdata</literal>
                and metadata,
                <indexterm><primary>metadata</primary></indexterm>
                separated by the different 
                <literal>SASentry</literal> blocks.
            </para>
            <indexterm>
                <primary>XML Stylesheet</primary>
                <secondary>cansasxml-html.xsl</secondary>
            </indexterm>
            <!-- too long for a DocBook "example" -->
            <informalexample>
                <!--<title><citetitle>cansasxml-html.xsl</citetitle></title>-->
                <programlisting language="xml" linenumbering="numbered">
                    <textobject>
                        <textdata fileref="../../cansasxml-html.xsl"/>
                    </textobject>
                </programlisting>
            </informalexample>
        </section>
    </section>
